         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is a detailed description of a class project for advanced managerial finance classes. The student estimates the weighted average cost of capital for an actual company, using primary data sources. The project develops skills (1) in using elementary financial management models, (2) in dealing with situations where there are too much or too little data, (3) in employing publicly available data sources and (4) in working around naturally occurring measurement errors.</p>
